/** @page component_readme Component Readme 

@section Component Specific Information

lmsensors/  
The PAPI lmsensors component requires lmsensors version >= 3.0.0.


How to install PAPI with the lmsensors component?
--------------------------------------------------

PAPI provides the following environment variables to specify the include and library path:

PAPI_LMSENSORS_ROOT  default /usr
PAPI_LMSENSORS_INC   default /usr/include/sensors
PAPI_LMSENSORS_LIB   default /usr/lib64

If you overwrite PAPI_LMSENSORS_ROOT, e.g.

export PAPI_LMSENSORS_ROOT = /software/lmsensors

PAPI will use the following configuration by default:
PAPI_LMSENSORS_INC = $PAPI_LMSENSORS_ROOT/include
PAPI_LMSENSORS_LIB = $PAPI_LMSENSORS_ROOT/lib64

If the include and library path does not match the scheme above you have to set the correct path for
PAPI_LMSENSORS_INC and PAPI_LMSENSORS_LIB.


Configure PAPI with lmsensors enabled.  
    % cd src
    % ./configure --prefix=some_location --with-components="lmsensors"
    % make


Before working with the lmsensors component, verify it's active by running
   % ./papi_component_avail"
and check if it listed under the "Active Components" list.

Note:
If the library libsensors.so cannot be found, you can use the runtime environment
variable PAPI_LMSENSORS_LIBNAME to set the correct path and library name, e.g.

export PAPI_LMSENSORS_LIBNAME = /usr/lib64/libsensors.so
